title: SEC Power Poll: Unbeaten LSU paces field
text:
SEC Power Poll: Unbeaten LSU paces field 
By Don Coble Thu, Oct 22, 2015 @ 9:51 pm | updated Thu, Oct 22, 2015 @ 9:54 pm Back Photo: 1 of 2 Next Bill Feig/The Advocate via AP LSU running back Leonard Fournette (7) carries for a touchdown against Florida during the first half of an NCAA college football game Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015, in Baton Rouge, La. Back Photo: 2 of 2 Next AP Texas A&M 's Kyle Allen looks to throw against Alabama during the first half of an NCAA college football game, Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015, in College Station, Texas. (AP Photo/Eric Gay) 
SEC POWER POLL 
QB Brandon Harris, RB Leonard Fournette league’s top one-two punch. 
2. ALABAMA (6-1) 
Crimson Tide facing Vols, then have bye week before showdown vs. LSU. 
3. FLORIDA (5-1) 
Gators actually gained greater legitimacy with tough loss at LSU. 
4. TEXAS A&M (5-1) 
Aggies’ success based on the ups and downs of QB Kyle Allen (above). 
5. OLE MISS (5-2) 
Memphis loss still doesn’t knock Rebels out of driver’s seat in West. 
6. MISSISSIPPI STATE (5-2) 
After two patsies in a row (Troy and Louisiana Tech), SEC wake-up call awaits. 
7. GEORGIA (5-2) 
Bye week allows Bulldogs to regroup for all-important game against Florida. 
8. AUBURN (4-2) 
Win at Kentucky was crucial and could save the season. 
9. KENTUCKY (4-2) 
Wildcats still in picture in inconsistent SEC East. 
Young Vols ready for the challenge of playing at ’Bama. 
11. MISSOURI (4-3) 
A 126th-ranked offense has dropped Tigers from nationally ranked to irrelevant. 
12. SOUTH CAROLINA (3-4) 
Tumultuous season found some footing with new coach Shawn Elliott. 
13. ARKANSAS (2-4) 
Razorbacks have allowed 14 plays of 30 or more yards. 
14. VANDERBILT (2-4) 
Starting QB Johnny McCray has more interceptions (10) than touchdowns (6). 
Don Coble The Times-Union
